<HEADLINE> Party for Overseas Students in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- "1999 New Year Celebration of
Overseas Students in Beijing" has been on stage tonight at Beijing
Century Theater.
</P>
<P>
Co-sponsored by the Ministry of Education and Beijing Municipal
Government, the party drew 1,200 overseas students from 50
countries such as the United States, Russia, Japan and the
People's Democratic Republic of Korea who presented their
performances in Chinese language and style, such as singing,
reciting poetries, Chinese humorous cross talk, Beijing Opera
and Kongfu.
</P>
<P>
From 1950 when the first 33 students from the then Eastern
Europe arrived in newly founded People's Republic of China to the
end of 1997, China had welcomed more than 271,000 overseas
students from more than 160 countries and regions. The number of
overseas students enjoyed a sharp rise from 1992 to 1996 with 30
percent increase by year. 
</P>
