<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Romania, Moldova Join Hands to Fight Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, November 4 (Xinhua) -- The security departments of
Ukraine, Romania and Moldova signed an agreement Thursday in
Cernovcy, a southwest city of Ukraine, to step up their
cooperation in battling transnational crime.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the three countries will make joint
efforts to prevent and combat terrorism, drug trafficking, money
laundering and other organized crimes.
</P>
<P>
The three countries' security departments will also cooperate
in cracking down on illegal selling of weapons, smuggling of the
cultural relics and illegal migration.
</P>
<P>
The three countries will also strengthen monitoring mechanism
for nuclear, chemical and biological weapons proliferation.
</P>
<P>
They have also agreed to set up an action group and facilitate
economic cooperation. 
</P>
