<HEADLINE> China Gets Tougher to Environment-destroying Institutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- China today outlawed any
construction projects which threaten environment by issuing a new
regulation aiming at constructors.
</P>
<P>
The regulation urges nationwide constructors to abide by
all the national and regional standards of pollutant discharge.
</P>
<P>
Environment-friendly materials and energy-saving equipment must
be used for industrial construction projects, the regulation said.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the regulation, any behavior to deteriorate
the environment will be curbed.
</P>
<P>
The state authorities in charge of construction and
environmental protection will introduce a new assessment mechanism
for effectively protecting environment.
</P>
<P>
Officials and experts will comprehensively and thoroughly
assess the effect of large projects which might do harm to the
environment.
</P>
<P>
All the constructors must submit detailed reports on
environment to environmental protection agencies for examination
and approval, the regulation said.
</P>
<P>
The highest environmental protection body under the State
Council will examine important projects such as nuclear power
plants, top-secret installations and trans-provincial facilities.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
