<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Moroccan Prime Minister (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- China hopes to advance the
existing friendship between the Chinese National People's Congress
(NPC) and the parliament of Morocco, said top-legislator Li
Peng.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, made this remark
during a meeting today with visiting Moroccan prime minister
Abderrahmane Youssoufi.
</P>
<P>
Youssoufi recalled his meeting with Li when he paid an
official visit to Morocco in 1995, and said that he was glad to
meet Li again.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed his gratitude to the Moroccan government and
people for their hospitality. He noted that China and Morocco
have witnessed the sound development of bilateral relations since
forging bilateral diplomatic ties, and as developing countries
there are no conflicts of interest between them, but rather
cooperation, understanding and friendship.
</P>
<P>
Li briefed the visitors on China's NPC system and invited
leaders of the Moroccan parliament to visit China.
</P>
<P>
Youssoufi said the Moroccan parliament has recently set up a
committee for the development of Morocco-China friendship.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981204.0062 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Moroccan Prime Minister (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In addition, the two sides exchanged views on the inauguration
of the euro currency and the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Youssoufi said that the integrity of European Union currencies
will benefit the EU nations and help stablize the financial
situation worldwide. However, he pointed out, small countries like
Morocco will encounter difficulties due to their increased debts
to European creditors.
</P>
<P>
Morocco has also been affected by the Asian financial crisis,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Li admitted that China was under great pressure and had to meet
difficulties because of the crisis. But the crisis is neither doing
overall damage to China's economy nor slowing sustained economic
development, he confirmed.
</P>
<P>
Li attributed this to China's increased economic strength due
to the reforms of the past two decades, effective governmental
measures, and China's rational foreign-debt structure.
</P>
<P>
Similar financial disturbances may appear again since an
unjust and irrational international political order still exists,
Li stressed.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he pointed, in the global economy China must keep
sight of the challenges as well as the opportunities, the
unfavorable as well as the favorable aspects.
</P>
<P>
The developing countries should learn to protect themselves and
avoid economic risks during this period of globalization, Li
advised. 
</P>
