<HEADLINE> Yugoslavian Legislators Approve Budget for 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavian legislators
approved a budget for 1999 on Thursday that amounts to 15.85
billion dinars (1.58 billion U.S.dollars).
</P>
<P>
The gross domestic product (GDP) in 1999 is estimated at about
174.3 billion dinars (17.43 billion dollars). The budget
expenditure represents 9.09 percent of the GDP next year.
</P>
<P>
Allocations for the ministries of defense and foreign affairs
will increase to 11 billion dinars and 600 million dinars.
</P>
<P>
The defense bill posted a 69 percent increase compared to the
1998 budget. It will account for about 6.33 percent of the GDP in
1999.
</P>
<P>
The diplomatic bill for the new fiscal year is equal to 0.3
percent of the 1999 GDP. 
</P>
