<HEADLINE> U.S. Envoy Starts Mediation Effort Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- U.S. special presidential
envoy Anthony Lake arrived here Friday on his third trip to the
Horn of Africa to seek a peaceful solution to the seven-month
border dispute between Ethiopia and Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
The office of Ethiopian government spokesperson Selome
Taddesse said here that former U.S. National Security Adviser
Lake will meet with Prime Minister Meles Zenawi Saturday to
facilitate a peaceful solution to the current Ethio-Eritrean
conflict.
</P>
<P>
The office said Lake's efforts will closely follow the line
given by the recent Organization of African unity (OAU) summit in
Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso.
</P>
<P>
"Ethiopia remains committed to a peaceful solution to the
crisis and appreciates the efforts made by Mr. Lake in this
regard," the office added.
</P>
<P>
The OAU summit mediation committee on Ethio-Eritrean border
dispute, held in Burkinabe capital on November 7 and 8, came up
with a set of proposals on the peaceful solution to the border
dispute.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has accepted the OAU proposals while Eritrea has
rejected the key element of the peace plan which calls for the
withdrawal of its troops from the disputed Badme area.
</P>
<P>
The proposals will be submitted to the summit of central organ
of OAU Mechanism for Conflict Prevention, Management and
Resolution scheduled to be held in Ouagadougou on December 17 and
18.
</P>
<P>
Lake has made two visits to Addis Ababa on October 8 and
November 11 this year for the resolution of the conflict in the
Horn of Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
