<HEADLINE> CIS Members See Industrial Production Slump </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, November 4 (Xinhua) -- Major member countries of the
Commonwealth of Independent States(CIS) saw their industrial
production in the first 10 months of 1998 drop drastically.
</P>
<P>
Russia's industrial production slid 4.6 percent over the same
period last year, with Ukraine 0.8 percent, Kazakhstan 1.6
percent, Armenia 1 percent and Moldova 8.1 percent, the Interfax
news agency quoted CIS statistics as saying.
</P>
<P>
But Belarus, Kyrgyzstan, Tajikistan, Azerbaijan and Georgia
have kept the momentum of industrial growth with an increase rate
of 9.9, 8.4, 7.1, 1.6, and 1 percent respectively over the same
period last year, according to the statistics.
</P>
<P>
Azerbaijan, Armenia and Georgia's gross domestic products (GDP)
increased 8.6, 8.5 and 6.4 percent respectively over the same
period last year, according to the statistics.
</P>
<P>
Belarus tops the CIS states in consumer price increases this
October with a 21 percent leap above prices last year. Russia and
Ukraine have kept a high inflation rate of 6.2 and 4.5 percent
respectively, the statistics show.
</P>
<P>
But Armenia enjoyed stable prices while Azerbaijan and
Kazakhstan saw their price drop. 
</P>
</TEXT>
