<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Attends Anti-Polio Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
today attended a national vaccination campaign to protect children
under the age of four against polio.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, accompanied by Health Minister Zhang Wenkang and Beijing
Mayor Jia Qinglin, administered polio vaccine pills to four
children at the Beixinhuajie Kindergarten in urban Beijing.
</P>
<P>
It has become a regular activity for high-ranking Chinese
officials to take part in the annual vaccinations to demonstrate
the government's strong support for the fight against polio.
</P>
<P>
The sixth round of the national immunization program will start
tomorrow and will last one month to ensure that children under four
are vaccinated.
</P>
<P>
Efforts made over the past five years have helped the country
approach the year-2000 goal of eradicating polio, which is also
the global goal established by the 41st World Health Conference
in 1988. 
