<HEADLINE> Army-run Businesses in Beijing Handed Over to Local Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua)--The People's Liberation Army
garrison in Beijing and the Beijing armed police force today
handed over 68 business entities to the local government.
</P>
<P>
This move is part of the process to implement the central
government's recent decision prohibiting the army, the armed
police and judicial departments from engaging in business
activities.
</P>
<P>
The 68 ventures, run by 14 PLA army units and the armed police
force in Beijing, has combined capital assets of 1.4 billion yuan
(about 170 million U.S. dollars) and 2,300 staff workers engaged
mainly in real estate, pharmaceuticals, trading, building
materials, storage and transportation and auto repairs.
</P>
<P>
The army and armed police officers attending the handover
ceremony held this afternoon said this divestiture represents the
basic completion of the local army's severance from business
activity.
</P>
<P>
These businesses will be surrendered to and operated by relevant
industries in the capital, according to Beijing municipal
government officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
