<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese-Launched European Satellite Handed Over to Users </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- A European-made satellite
launched by a Chinese rocket on July 18 this year became available
to its users today.
</P>
<P>
The satellite, the Sino No-1, is the first commercial
telecommunications satellite managed by the Sino Satellite
Communications Company Ltd of China, which is engaged in the
leasing of satellite transponders and other aspects of the
satellite telecommunications business.
</P>
<P>
The satellite, manufactured by Aerospatiale of France, carries
24 C-band transponders which cover the entire Asia-Pacific region,
and 14 KU-band transponders which cover China and its neighboring
countries.
</P>
<P>
Users of the satellite include the Civil Aviation
Administration of China, the People's Bank of China and the
Shanghai Satellite TV Station.
</P>
<P>
Sino-1 is the first European-made satellite launched by a
Chinese rocket, and the first foreign satellite monitored and
managed by China.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that the satellite is operating normally and all
functions meeting design requirements.
</P>
<P>
The satellite has an effective life of 17 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
