<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kyrgyzstan to Crackdown on Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Kyrgyzstan Prime Minister
Kubanychbek Zhumaliyev signed a decree on Thursday ordering a
crackdown on smuggling and intensification of import and export
inspections to protect the country's domestic markets.
</P>
<P>
Under the decree, Kyrgyzstan's state departments responsible
for national security, law enforcement and tax collection will work to
strengthen the inspection of import and export products.
</P>
<P>
They were also granted the right to confiscate smuggled goods
to improve their facilities or reward the activists who expose the
crimes.
</P>
<P>
Kyrgyzstan will also amend its customs law and relevant
anti-smuggling laws by imposing more stern punishment for
smugglers.
</P>
<P>
The decree meanwhile demands that government functionaries set
an example in enforcing the laws when investigating a smuggling
case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
