<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Moroccan Prime Minister (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese president Jiang Zemin
said that China values its exchanges and cooperation with Morocco,
and will, taking the 40th anniversary of bilateral diplomatic ties
as a new starting point, make joint efforts with Morocco to bring
a better bilateral relationship into the next century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark here this afternoon in a meeting with
visiting Moroccan Prime Minister Abderrahmane Youssoufi who is
here on a five-day official visit at the invitation of Chinese
premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his pleasure at meeting with Youssoufi, Jiang asked
Youssoufi to convey his regards to King Hassan II of Morocco and
invited the king to visit China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed to the positive and fruitful talks Thursday
between the prime ministers of the two countries who reached
wide-ranging consensus on furthering bilateral reciprocal
cooperation on an equal footing in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Youssoufi's current visit to China is a great event
in bilateral relations, Jiang voiced his hope that Youssoufi will
learn more about China through this visit.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that since the two countries forged diplomatic ties,
they have scored remarkable results in their cooperation in
various fields including politics, economy, culture and
health-care.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have also understood and supported each other
in international affairs, and the Chinese side is
satisfied with this, added Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that with the development of
multi-polarization and economic globalization upon the approach
of a new century, Sino-Moroccan relations are faced with some new
situations and the two sides should further explore new means for
bilateral cooperation.
</P>
