<HEADLINE> Dos Santos to Be Only Candidate for Party Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The 8th session of the Central
Committee of the ruling People's Liberation Movement of Angola
(MPLA) has said Angolan President Jose Eduardo dos Santos has
been chosen as the only candidate for the party chairmanship.
</P>
<P>
In its communique issued here Friday, the 8th session of the
MPLA central committee which just ended Thursday night made the
decision. It also decided to hold MPLA's 4th National Congress
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 8th session of the MPLA central committee expressed "great
concern" over the crisis in the Angolan peace process.
</P>
<P>
It attributed the faltering peace process to the "obstinate
obstruction" by Jonas Savimbi, president of the opposition
National Union for Total Independence of Angola (UNITA), calling
him a "war criminal."
</P>
<P>
The MPLA central committee reiterated that the Angolan
government will cut any relation with the "armed wing of UNITA"
and will only have dialog and cooperate with the peace-loving
UNITA Renovation Commission in completing the 1994 Lusaka Peace
Protocol.
</P>
<P>
The communique noted that the forthcoming party congress will
discuss the "serious social and economic situation" facing Angola
and work out a program for the economic development in the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the MPLA national congress is "MPLA and the
Challenge in 21st Century."
</P>
<P>
Angola launched its privatization process in 1991. However,
almost all of the privatized state enterprises are controlled by
foreigners and the Angolan national economy is on the brink of
collapse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
