<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 4 (Xinhua) -- China has earmarked 150 billion
yuan (18 billion U.S. dollars) worth of accumulation funds for
housing this year, officials said today.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate that China will see a profitable housing
market, but first the state must adopt laws and regulations
accordingly.
</P>
<P>
China has introduced a series of reform measures in this
industry since 1978, and to date some one-billion square meters
of housing has been completed.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the construction fund accounted for 26.6
percent of total investment in fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
After the authorities encouraged people to buy their own
housing, the system of accumulation funds, which will financially
aid these buyers, was initiated.  
