<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Cuts Interest Rates by 0.25 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Association of
Banks Friday decided to lower deposit rates by 0.25 percent to 4.5
percent, the second interest rate cut within two weeks.
</P>
<P>
The Association of Banks made the announcement after its
committee meeting here Friday, saying that the move was made in
response to the lower prevailing market cost of funds.
</P>
<P>
Starting from next Monday, the rate for both savings and 24
hours' Call/ Notice will be 4.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's major banks, the Hongkong and Shanghai Banking
Corporation Ltd, Standard Chartered, Bank of China Hong Kong
Branch and Hang Seng Bank, also announced Friday to reduce their
prime lending rates by 0.25 percent to 9.25 percent from next
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Association of Banks made the last rate cut on November 23,
1998, also by 0.25 percent. 
