<HEADLINE> China Enjoys Improved Air Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Air pollution indexes for most
Chinese cities fell over the past week, according to the weekly
report issued by the China Environmental Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen, Zhanjiang, Ningbo, Haikou, Beihai, Xiamen, Wenzhou
and Shantou enjoyed excellent air quality between November 27 and
December 3, with 19 cities, including Shanghai, Qingdao and
Qinhuangdao, reporting good air quality.
</P>
<P>
Experts attribute the improved air quality to favorable weather
conditions. Rain and snow in south, east and north China has
helped reduce pollutants in the air, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Twelve cities, including Chongqing, Tianjin and Guangzhou,
reported slight air pollution during the period, with Beijing,
Taiyuan and Guiyang reporting moderate pollution.
</P>
<P>
Lanzhou, Xining, Urumqi and Hohhot reported serious air
pollution, with high levels of suspended particles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
