minutes 28.89 seconds. The bronze medal went to Li's teammate An
Yulong in 2:29.02.
</P>
<P>
Yang Yang (A), who was ranked fifth both in the 1,500m and
overall rankings at 74 and 75 points respectively before this
leg, cliamed the women's 1,500m gold Saturday in 2:34.97. The
victory secured her first position in the individual overall
standings.
</P>
<P>
Choi Min-Kyung of South Korea was second in 2:35.17, followed
by China's Yang Yang (S) in 2:35.79.
</P>
<P>
Among the six-player women's final, Wang Chunlu of China,
former world champion in the 500m and 1,000m, was disqualified
because of foul.
</P>
<P>
Daniel Weimstein of the United States also fouled out in the
men's 1,000 meters final.
</P>
<P>
The ongoing World Cup Beijing leg is drawing skaters from 11
countries and regions to take part and is to be end on Sunday.
</P>
