<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed higher on
Singapore Stock Market Friday after fluctuating up and down all
day .
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) edged up 13.70 points
to close at 1,357.13 points.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover shrank to 205.54 million units valued at
362.70 million Singapore dollars (219.91 million U.S. dollars).
there were 121 decliners against 119 advancers with 180 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
ST Engg remained at the top of today's actives chart as it had
13.30 million units traded. It was followed by Van DH that had
10.88 million shares done. DBS Land was next with 9.09 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
HKL led the ascent of the day with a seven-cent rise to 1.42
U.S. dollars. Cerebos gained six cents to end at 2.72 Singapore
dollars. InchMarket moved up six cent to finish at 0.79 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Venture headed the descent of the day as it
dropped 20 cents to 6.05 Singapore dollars. UOB F sank 15 cents to
9.40 Singapore dollars. RothmansI retreated 10 cents to end at
9.05 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
The market opened lower in reaction to Wall Street's decline
but rebounded to an intra-day high of 1058 points. By the last
hour of trading, the market had nearly shed all its gains, but
rallied up in the last few minutes
</P>
<P>
Dealers said light volume and dearth of fresh news contributed
to the volatility.  
</P>
