<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Minister of State for Health
and Family Welfare Dalit Ezhilmalai said Friday that as many as
6,609 AIDS cases have been reported from various parts of India as
on October 31 this year.
</P>
<P>
In a written reply to questions in the on-going session of the
Upper House of Parliament here, he said Maharashtra State headed
the AIDS list accounting for 3,251 cases.
</P>
<P>
Greater emphasis had been given to create awareness about AIDS
in the country and awareness levels on AIDS are of the order of 68
to 94 percent on an average in selected metros and between 22 to
72 percent in selected rural areas in the country, Ezhilmlai said.
</P>
<P>
A national plan had been launched for educating and sensitizing
the youth through school-based programs on AIDS, he said. 
