retail investors' expectation over the reported business mergers
between Daewoo and Samsung and other top five chaebols continued
to be positive, heralding the return of institutional and foreign
buying.
</P>
<P>
Expectations on the upcoming talks between the heads of the top
five conglomerates -- Hyundai, Daewoo, Samsung, LG and SK -- and
the South Korean government on their business restructuring, along
with the appreciation of the Japanese yen against the U.S. dollar,
sparked investors to buy top five-affiliated stocks, said a stock
analyst. 
