<DOCNO> XIE19981204.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Formulates New Approach to Develop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 4 (Xinhua) --Singapore Trade Development
Board (TDB) Friday announced it will go full stream ahead in its
efforts to expand the country's external trade wing with a
three-prong approach to access new markets.
</P>
<P>
Director of TDB International Operations Goh Oon Tong told a
press conference that TDB will step up efforts to access new
markets, to consolidate resource in regional markets and to expand
demand in growth markets.
</P>
<P>
TDB defines U.S., EU, Australia, China and India as growth
markets, bills the Middle East, Central Asia, Latin America,
Africa, Central and Eastern Europe as emerging markets, and places
U.S, EU Japan, Malaysia and Hong Kong in positions of five top
markets.
</P>
<P>
In its three-prong approach, TDB will help companies diversify
their markets and is planning 28 fairs and missions to the
emerging markets in 1999 to explore new markets and sectors such
as textiles, logistics and packaging in Latin America.
</P>
<P>
TDB also plans to open up new offices next year to strengthen
its presence in the emerging markets and to be in a better
position to help companies seek business opportunities.
</P>
<P>
On regional markets, TDB reaffirms it remain optimistic about
the region's potential and will continue to identify investment
and trade opportunities in the respective countries.
</P>
<P>
Concerning the growth markets, TDB will concentrate its efforts
to increase demand by identifying business opportunities in and
focus on niche industries and new activities.
</P>
<P>
TDB plans to organize 33 fairs and missions to the United
States and EU in 1999 to help companies explore new activities
such as procurement, franchising and direct marketing
</P>
<P>
On a whole, the first ten months this year saw healthy and
positive growth in Singapore's exports to the growth markets and
emerging markets respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, during the first ten months, Singapore's export to
regional ASEAN markets, Hong Kong, Japan as well as Latin America
showed a decline.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
