points, or 0.83 percent, to close at 9,963.14 Friday.
</P>
<P>
Market turnover was 4.510 billion HK dollars (578 million U.S.
dollars), 1.096 billion HK dollars (141 million U.S. dollars) less
than that of Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index (HSI) fell 21.70 points, or 0.22
percent, to open at 10,024.45 Friday morning. It then edged up
6.42 points, or 0.06 percent, to close the morning session at
10,052.57.
</P>
<P>
The HSI entered the week's trading at 10,705.19 Monday, 0.34
percent lower than the close last Friday. It then lost over 700
points to below 10,000-point mark due to the influence of the Wall
Street falls in the first two days of the week.
</P>
<P>
The index remained fluctuating around the 10,000 point in the
heel of the unstable overseas market since a slight rebound of
0.80 percent on Wednesday. It fell 9.63 points, or 0.10 percent,
to close at 10,046.15 Thursday. 
