<HEADLINE> Reshuffle of Basketball Players Possible </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Basketball teams in
competition at the 13th Asian Games are allowed to reshuffle or
change players even after they have submitted lists to the
games. However, the changes must be sought before the matches
begin.
</P>
<P>
This was confirmed by Dr. Prathum Muangmee, sports manager
for basketball, after there was some confusion among basketball
team managers over whether the players could be changed.
</P>
<P>
"I reaffirm that the rules of the Asian Basketball
Confederation allow such changes providing team managers meet
before and approve the substitutions," he said.
</P>
<P>
Team managers will meet on Saturday at 2:00 pm at The
Raddison Hotel, during which changes of players can be sought.
However, all players must be certified by their own National
Olympic Committee and the ABC, he said.
</P>
<P>
Dr, Prathum pointed out that the ABC complies with the
International Basketball Federation. "In fact, we have notified
all the teams that such changes are possible upon their
notification to the team managers' meeting," he added.
</P>
<P>
Certification by a national Olympic committee is to ensure
that basketball players are truly from the countries and regions
they claim to represent. After that, they need to have ID Cards
to be eligible for competition, Dr. Prathum explained. 
</P>
</TEXT>
