<HEADLINE> Zambian Police Smash Vehicle Racket </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Police in Zambia's capital have
smashed a racket issuing vehicle registration certificates on
stolen vehicles, according to Friday's Times of Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted police spokesman Alex Chilufya as saying
Thursday that some policemen from the Road Traffic Commission
have been suspected of being involved in the crime.
</P>
<P>
Three suspects have been arrested, a car impounded and four
certificates have also been confiscated, according to the
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The mastermind of the racket is on the run together with an
accomplice, Chilufya said.
</P>
<P>
He said some police officers, immigration and customs
officers, road traffic officers have been suspected to be
involved in the case in which some vehicles stolen from Zambia
are sold in its neighboring countries and vice versa.  
