<HEADLINE> Thailand Maintain Perfect Record at Asiad football </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANNGKOK, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Hosts Thailand maintained a
perfect record after beating Oman 2-0 in a Group F match at
Suphachalasai Stadium on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The host team, which beat Hong Kong of China 5-0 in their first
group match, totally outplayed their Oman opponents and took an
early 2-0 lead at half time.
</P>
<P>
Worawoot Srimaka opened the scoring at the 13th minute after
completing a quick counter-attack with a right-footer just inside
the penalty area.
</P>
<P>
T. Damrong-Ongtrakul made it 2-0 for the host country at the
40th minute, again thanks to their effective counter-attack.
</P>
<P>
Srimaka got a yellow card in the second half and hit the post
once. He had several more scoring chances but failed to grasp any
of them.
</P>
<P>
The Oman team, which beat Hong Kong of China 6-0 in their first
outing at the 13th Asian Games, appeared tiring early in the match
and could not match the pace of the host team.
</P>
<P>
Their defence line looked weak while their forwards could not
get the support they badly needed from their teammates as the
mid-field was dominated by the Thai team.
</P>
<P>
In a Group Pool A match played on Friday, South Korea trounced
Vietnam 4-0.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans, one of the favorites of the tournament,
proved they are still the title contenders despite they lost to
Uzbekistan 2-3 in their first match.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans squandered a 2-0 lead in the match against
Uzbekistan to concede three goals in a row in the second half.
</P>
<P>
But in the match against Vietnam, the South Korean team
shrugged off the shadow and dominated the match from the very
beginning.
</P>
<P>
By halftime, the South Koreans were already 2-0 up and they
went on to score two more goals in the second half to seal up
their group competitions with a sweet victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
