<HEADLINE> S.Korean Presidential Security Office to Go On-line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Presidential Security Office
of South Korea will open its own Web site on the Internet next
Monday, a spokesman for the office said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The web site opening is part of the efforts by South Korean
President Kim Dae-jung to shake off the authoritarian image
formed in the past governments, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Organization, functions and duties of the Presidential Security
Office will be put on the Web site.
</P>
<P>
The Web site will create a "dialogue forum" to which the public
can send questions and suggestions regarding the office's
activities. It will also offer some basics of "self-defense"
techniques for women and youths.
</P>
<P>
The Web site, which is linked to the presidential palace Chong
Wa Dae Web site, located at www.cwd.go.kr, can also be contacted
directly at www.cwd.go.kr/security. 
</P>
