<HEADLINE> Mongolia to Further Develop Relations With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia will develop a 21st
century-oriented relationship with China based on equality, mutual
benefit and non-interference, said Mongolian President Nachagyn
Bagabandy.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua on eve of a state visit to China,
Bagabandy said that his talks with Chinese leaders will help
deepen mutual trust and promote cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The president stressed that his visit aims to set principles
that will govern the overall bilateral relations and cooperation
in the new century.
</P>
<P>
He said during his visit, he will reaffirm that the government
of the People's Republic of China is the sole legitimate
government of China, and that Taiwan is an inalienable part of the
Chinese territory.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia will not establish official relations with Taiwan and
its contacts with Taiwan will be confined to trade, economic,
cultural and humanitarian cooperation, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian government always respects China's position on
the Taiwan issue and opposes Taiwan's efforts to join the United
Nations, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
