<DOCNO> XIE19981204.0183 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Duma to Present New START-II Bill to President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Russian State Duma is
expected to submit to President Boris Yeltsin a new bill on the
ratification of the START-II treaty on banning intercontinental
ballistic missiles (ICBM) in Russia and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Under the original treaty, the two countries will destroy all
their multiple-warhead ICBMs by 2003 and cut the number of
single-warhead ICBMs on both sides to between 3000-3500.
</P>
<P>
In the new version, "Russia's military doctrine is to be
implemented, and it is Russia's policy to create new weapons so
that the national security can be completely ensured," said Duma
speaker Gennady Seleznyov.
</P>
<P>
The new bill, prepared by three key committees of Duma, will be
sent to Yeltsin after being deliberated within Duma until December
8.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. ratified the START-II treaty in January 1996, but the
Russian Duma, the lower house of Russian parliament, has
repeatedly refused to discuss the treaty, claiming it would put
Russia at a strategic disadvantage compared with the U.S. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981204.0184 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Light Plane Crashlands in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- A single engine light plane
crashlanded early Friday on an airstrip in Davao, the Southern
Philippines, injuring two pilots on board, the Air Transportation
Office here said.
</P>
<P>
The office said a sprayer aircraft plowed through Dapco
airstrip in Panabo, Davao, after its wing hit an electric wire
along the way down.
</P>
<P>
The two pilots of the plane were injured in the incident and
brought to a nearby hospital for treatment, it said. 
</P>
