<DOCNO> XIE19981204.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Revenue up in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Recent statistics show that
Shanghai's industrial and commercial revenues grew by 15.49-fold
to 84.1 billion yuan in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The ratio of revenue from the tertiary industry has jumped by
55.4 percent over the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
Tax revenues from foreign enterprises soared 7.59-fold from 2.5
billion yuan in 1993 to 21.4 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
State-owned enterprises in the manufacturing and construction
sectors paid taxes of over 25.4 billion yuan last year, or close
to 30 percent of the total. Taxes paid by private businesses grew
from less than 100 million yuan in 1987 to 2.8 billion yuan in
1997.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai currently has 352,000 taxpayers, a 42-fold rise on the
1978 figure. Enterprises under public ownership account for 42
percent of the total number of taxpayers, with private business
accounting for 48 percent, foreign-funded firms 5.2 percent and
shareholding firms the remainder. 
</P>
</TEXT>
