<HEADLINE> Iran Starts Massive Military Maneuvers in Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Iran's elite Islamic
Revolutionary Guards Corps (IRGC) and the Army started joint
military maneuvers in the Gulf and the Gulf of Oman early Friday
morning, Tehran radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The war games, code-named "Vahdat-77" (Unity-77), is being
carried out from the strategically important Strait of Hormuz at
the mouth of the Persian Gulf to the waters close to Chabahar in
the Gulf of Oman.
</P>
<P>
About 20,000 troops would be participating in the five-day
military exercises and some Omani military experts will observe
the maneuvers, earlier report said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the official news agency IRNA on Friday quoted
spokesman for the war games Brigadier General Issa Golvadi as
saying the maneuvers are for peace and security in the region,
once it gets free from foreign military presence.
</P>
<P>
The change of the code-name from "Victory" to "Vahdat-77" is a
sign of Iran's full confidence and trust in the broadening of deep
relations on defense issues with regional countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Terming the move as a goodwill to the Gulf states, the
spokesman said that before the start of the war games, six shells
will be fired as a salute in honor of the Gulf countries. 
</P>
