<HEADLINE> Tianjin Assists Three Gorges Relocation Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The north China municipality
of Tianjin has provided substantial assistance for relocation
efforts and local economic development in the Three Gorges Area.
</P>
<P>
The municipality has invested some 650 million yuan in a number
of economic and technological projects which have created sizable
profits for enterprises in the area.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin and the Three Gorges Area have effectively integrated
their unique advantages in terms of resources, technology and
products in order to develop a number of products of short supply
on the domestic market.
</P>
<P>
A number of Tianjin enterprises established cooperative
relations with counterparts in the Three Gorges Area. The
municipality has provided technology and equipment, with the Three
Gorges Area providing production bases and markets.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has also provided training for workers in the area, and
has built two new primary schools enabled some 1,000 dropouts to
return to school. Some four million yuan in funding from the
municipal government has been used to support economic
construction in the area, according to local sources. 
</P>
