<HEADLINE> Indian Government Likely to Put More Public Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government is
considering putting 23 more public sector undertakings (PSUs) on
the disinvestment list as part of its program to privatize all
PSUs except those relating to defense and national security, a
senior official said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The government was going ahead with disinvestment of five PSUs
and another 23 had been recommended for the purpose. In the next
four to five years the government would likely get out of all
state-owned industries except those concerned with defense and
national security. This would cut losses, reduce bureaucratic
interference in their functioning and encourage competition.
</P>
<P>
The exercise for selling shares of Videsh Sanchar Nigam Ltd
(telephone sector) and the Gas Authority of India Ltd is going on.
23 more PSUs are meant for both strategic sale and privatization.
This apart, eight state-owned units will be closed and seven
others have already been recommended for strategic sale, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
