<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain to Invest 2 Billion U.S. Dollars in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Spain will provide a line
of credit of up to two billion U.S. dollars to support its exports
and investment to Mexico under an economic and financial
cooperation agreement signed on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The accord, inked by visiting Spanish Economy Minister Rodrigo
Rato and the Mexican side, also foresees that Spain could donate
up to 10 million dollars to fund projects through the Spanish
Foreign Trade Institute and the Official Credit Institute.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, the Spanish minister met with Mexican
President Ernesto Zedillo and held talks with Finance Minister
Jose Angel Gurria and Commerce Minister Herminio Blanco. 
</P>
