<HEADLINE> Bosnian Serb Republic Protests at Arrest of General by SFOR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Nikola Poplasen, president of
the Bosnian Serb Republic, Thursday strongly protested against the
arrest of the republic's most senior military figure, Radislav
Krstic, by the multinational Stabilization Force (SFOR).
</P>
<P>
General Krstic, commander of the 5th Corps of the Bosnian Serb
Army, was arrested on his way to a general staff meeting near
Bijeljina, in the north of the Bosnian Serb republic controlled by
U.S. troops serving in SFOR, around midday Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
