with Carlos Westendorp, envoy of the peace implementation council
of Bosnia, Poplasen called the SFOR operation a "traditional
terrorist act," noting that it went beyond the mandate entrusted
to SFOR under the Dayton Peace Accord and violated elementary
requirements of international law. 
