<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Prime Minister
Chuan Leekpai has expressed concern over Bangkok's traffic
during the 13th Asian Games which open on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"I'm afraid that there may be congestion on the roads during
the opening and closing days, though it is likely to be less so
during the other days of the Games," Leekpai said.
</P>
<P>
