<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Initiates Special Training for Housemaids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 4 (Xinhua) -- A special housekeeping training
program for Sri Lankan housemaids seeking employment abroad has
been initiated by the Sri Lanka Bureau of Foreign Employment
(SLBFE), the SLBFE disclosed Friday.
</P>
<P>
Under this program all Sri Lankan housemaids seeking foreign
employment will have to undergo this special training course at 15
centers established islandwide, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The program is expected to enable housemaids to acquire a
knowledge of problems faced by women while being employed abroad
in addition to expanding their knowledge of housekeeping and the
use of sophisticated household items.
</P>
<P>
Additionally it will help housemaids to find solutions to their
 family problems faced by dependents when they are employed
abroad.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the SLBFE noted that Sri Lanka's earnings from
private remittances have exceeded 637 million U.S. dollars during
the first eight months of 1998 in comparison to 563 dollars during
the same period the previous year.
</P>
<P>
It added that there has been an increasing demand for Sri
Lankan skilled labor especially in the Middle East where there is
an influx of housemaids and domestic laborers from Asian
countries. 
</P>
