<HEADLINE> Vietnam Has 4-4.5 Million Disabled People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam, with the population of
78 million, has 4-4.5 million disabled people, of whom 1.5 million
are children, official media here reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
However, only 10-15 percent of these disabled people have
access to functional rehabilitation services.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Public Health and the Functional Rehabilitation
Association have adopted a program to provide functional
rehabilitation for the disabled on the occasion of the
International Day for the Disabled.
</P>
<P>
The program sets the target to provide functional
rehabilitation treatment to all disabled people in Vietnam and
proper education to all disabled children of school age by the
year 2020.
</P>
<P>
In the immediate future, the program will be implemented in
3,000 communes in 50 provinces and cities. 
</P>
