<HEADLINE> Hun Sen to Visit Vietnam Before ASEAN Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen
is scheduled to pay a two-day official visit to Vietnam on
December 13-14 as guest of Vietnam's Prime Minister Phan Van Khai,
according to official sources here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The visit is arranged a few days before the sixth ASEAN summit
meeting to be held in Hanoi.
</P>
<P>
Cambodian ambassador to Vietnam Nuon Sareth said the official
visit to Vietnam will be the first trip abroad made by Hun Sen
since he became prime minister of the new coalition government in
Cambodia a few days ago.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources here said Hun Sen's visit to Vietnam aims at
strengthening and consolidating bilateral friendship cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen and Vietnam's leaders are expected to discuss measures
to solve outstanding issues related to their land and sea borders,
and to the Vietnamese community residing in Cambodia, the sources
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
