<HEADLINE> Injury Forced Chinese Gymnast out of Asiad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese gymnast Lu Yufu
pulled out of the 13th Asian Games because of knee injury he
sustained Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Lu, member of the 1997 world champion team,
tore his knee ligament in pratice Wednesday afternoon. He will
be very likely replaced by Zhao Sheng.
</P>
<P>
Lu jumped to internatinal fame in the East Asian Games last
year, where he won three gold medals in team, floor exercises and
pommel horse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
