<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Needs $4.5M to Dispose Obsolete </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 3 (xinhua) -- Ethiopia Thursday said
that along with the Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) it is
looking for donors to fund the 4.5 million U.S. Dollars needed to
dispose obsolete pesticides in the country.
</P>
<P>
Bateno Kabeto, an official from the Ethiopian Ministry of
Agriculture, told a meeting here that there are 1,152 tons of
obsolete pesticides and more than 100 tons of contaminated
equipment and soil in the country.
</P>
<P>
The official said some of these chemicals are over 40 years
old while some have become unrecognized as their labels were lost
or mixed up with a cocktail of different types of pesticides.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting, Alemayehu Wodajeneh, FAO's obsolete
pesticide coordinator, said that Morocco is at the top followed
by Ethiopia and Tanzania in obsolete pesticide stock in Africa.
</P>
<P>
He said that 80 to 100 million Dollars is needed to dispose
expired pesticides in Africa. 
</P>
