<HEADLINE> IFC Finances Brazil's Automotive Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) Thursday announced its agreement to provide 47
million U.S. dollars in financing to Industrias Arteb S.A., a
Brazilian manufacturer of automotive lighting components.
</P>
<P>
Arteb produces head and tail lamps and other lighting
components for automakers in Brazil and Argentina. The 118 million
dollar project will install new operating capacity and replace
outdated technology in Arteb's existing plant in Sao Paulo. The
financing will also enhance the company's financial structure and
pay for the construction of two new plants in Gravatai, Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The financing package includes a loan of 20 million dollars for
the IFC's own account and a loan of 20 million dollars for the
account of participants. The IFC is also making an equity
investment of 7 million dollars for a 7.8 percent stake in the
company.
</P>
<P>
The IFC is member of the World Bank Group and also regarded as
the largest multilateral source of lending for private sectors
in developing countries. 
