<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves 600 Mln Dlrs to Back Economic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Thursday
approved 600 million U.S. dollars in loans to assist the
Philippines in its efforts for economic recovery.
</P>
<P>
The banking system reform project, private enterprise credit
support project and third rural finance project are designed to
combat the effects of the East Asian financial crisis by
strengthening the country's banking system, enhancing private
sector development and creating jobs and sustaining basic social
services.
</P>
<P>
These projects form part of the 1 billion dollar package
pledged to the Philippines by the president of the World Bank,
James D. Wolfensohn, during his visit to Manila early this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
