<HEADLINE> Paerson Wins World Cup Slalom Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Anja Paerson of Sweden won
a women's World Cup slalom Thursday in California, the United
States.
</P>
<P>
Paerson, a 17-year-old World Cup rookie, stunned a veteran
field by coming from 15th place to the first today, combining 1
minute, 40.84 seconds in her two runs.
</P>
<P>
She clocked 48.82 seconds in the afternoon session, 1.08
seconds faster than anyone else.
</P>
<P>
Australia's Zali Steggall, the Olympic slalom bronze medalist
last years, was beaten into second by 0.1 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Ingrid Salvenmoser of Austria, seventh after the first run,
claimed third in 1:41.29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
