<HEADLINE> Tianjin Building Natural-Gas Power Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a
330-million-yuan natural gas power plant has begun in the largest
north China port city of Tianjin, the first of its kind ever built
locally.
</P>
<P>
With some 50,000 square meters of floor space, the Binhai
Natural Gas Power Plant is near a natural gas processing plant and
will be a major consumer of natural gas from the Bohai Sea.
</P>
<P>
The power plant will install units with a combined capacity of
250,000 kw, and is expected to ease local power supply shortages.
</P>
<P>
The oil fields in western part of the Bohai Sea went into
operation in 1997 and have an annual production capacity of
500,000 tons of oil and up to 400,000 cubic meters of natural
gas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
