<HEADLINE> Qingdao Accelerates Urban Infrastructure Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The coastal city of Qingdao in
east China's Shandong Province plans to invest a record 2.93
billion yuan on urban infrastructure construction projects next
year.
</P>
<P>
Related funds will be used for 20 projects in nine areas
ranging from highways, urban afforestation and controlling river
pollution to the development of parks and the expansion of waste
disposal and water plants.
</P>
<P>
Completion of the most ambitious project development package in
the city's history is expected to greatly enhance its image and
substantially improve environmental conditions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
