<HEADLINE> DPR Korea Withdraws Women's Basketball Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 4 (Xinhua) -- As DPR Korea withdrew its
women's basketball team in the last minutes, the adjustments in
groupings have been made for the 13th Asian Games to be started
here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In order to avoid confusion, the remaining eight women's squads
are halved into two groups of Group E and F after the men's teams
are divided into four groups of A, B, C and D.
</P>
<P>
The new adjustments see the shift of the Philippines from Group
E to F after the withdrawal of DPR Korean women cagers.
</P>
<P>
Group E now includes South Korea, Chinese Taipei, Kazakhstan
and Thailand, while Group F pitches Japan against China,
Kyrgyzstan and the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The previous groupings were based on the Asian seedings as
South Korea ranked first, followed by Japan, China, Chinese
Taipei, DPR Korea and Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
"When DPR Korea pulled out its women's team, Kazakhstan moved
up to fifth seed, and host Thailand chooses its place in Group E
under the ruling of the International Basketball Federation," said
Sakchye Tabsuwan, chief of technical sub-committee.
</P>
<P>
Thus, only the Philippines and Kyrgyzstan become the remaining
unseeded teams with the former pitted in Group F in the late draw.
</P>
