<HEADLINE> Bulgaria to Cut Import Duties in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Bulgarian government is to
cut most import duties from January 1, 1999, in a bid to revive
its economy, according to a senior customs official.
</P>
<P>
The tariff reduction will be made on almost all imported goods
that Bulgaria itself does not produce, said Plamen Minev, chief of
the General Customs Directorate, following a cabinet meeting.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria's average tariff in 1999 will be 15.58 percent,
compared to 17.25 percent in 1997 and 16.18 in 1998. The downward
tendency will continue in the next two years so as to reach the
standard in the European countries where duties charged on
industrial goods average 4.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
