percent and those on petrol will drop from 25 to 22.5 percent.
Such imports as breeding animals, soy oil, and baby milks and
foods will be exempt from tariffs.
</P>
<P>
Also on the reduction list will be a number of industrial
goods, with the highest at 35 percent. The reduction, however,
does not cover ready-made clothes, shoes, household utensils and
automobiles.
</P>
<P>
Almost all articles under the information technologies
agreement within the World Trade Organization, all raw materials
(apart from oil), medical equipment and medicines will be exempt
from customs charges.
</P>
<P>
The tariff on wheat, pork, sunflower oils and proteins for
fodder production are temporarily reduced in order to keep the
home market balance in conditions of liberal export regulations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
