<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Plague Claims Seven Lives in East Kazakhstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of the plague in
eastern Kazakhstan has killed seven people and infected more than
600 others, the Interfax News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Between 40 and 50 people are believed to be infected everyday
in the East Kazakhstan state capital of Ust-Kamenogorsk as the
disease spreads rapidly through the population.
</P>
<P>
The Kazakh government has been forced to import medicines to
fight the plague as none of the Commonwealth of Independent States
has ever produced drugs for the disease.
</P>
<P>
A fire which destroyed 90,000 hectares of forest in east
Kazakhstan last year drove huge numbers of rodents out of their
usually habitat into residential areas where they passed diseases
to domestic animals and people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
