<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Pro Athletes Expected to Get Tax Breaks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Canadian professional sports
teams and athletes should get tax breaks from the government, a
parliamentay report recommends here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A sport franchise could be eligible for a tax credit of about
3.2 million U.S. dollars on its first revenues of 32 million
dollars, and teams with higher revenues would be subject to a
lower rate.
</P>
<P>
It is also recommended that pro athletes should have a lesser
tax burden to resemble the U.S. system.
</P>
<P>
The report was represented to the House of Commons Thursday.
But all four opposition parties said giving tax breaks to
millionaire teams and athletes is unacceptable. 
</P>
