<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Net Foreign Exchange Reserves Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's net foreign
exchange reserves declined by 1.8 million U.S. dollars to 14.21
billion U.S. dollars in the week ended November 30, the Jakarta
Post Friday quoted a statement from Bank Indonesia as reporting.
</P>
<P>
The decline was due mainly to repayment of part of the
government's overseas debt, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
However, reserves were still well above the adjusted target
agreed with the International Monetary Fund, which stands at 11.26
billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
