<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tourism Booms in East China's Shandong Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The tourism industry in east
China's Shandong Province reported an annual growth of 29.3
percent in the number of overseas visitors and that of 33.5
percent in the income from catering them, in the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The income of the domestic tourism sector also soared 92
percent on a yearly basis in the period.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province reaped 23 billion yuan in income,
accounting for 3.46 percent of the province's GDP.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 21.4 billion yuan stemmed from the year's 54.88
million domestic visitors to Shandong, with the rest coming from
580,000 overseas tourists.
</P>
<P>
During the two decades of China's reforms and opening-up since
1978, the number of domestic visitors has amounted to 400 million,
and that of overseas tourists reached 3.42 million.
</P>
<P>
The province now has over 500 scenic spots, more than 130
hotels of various classes, and more than 150 travel services, 45
of which handle international tourism and have contracts with more
than 150 overseas travel services.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has also used over 300 million U.S. dollars of
overseas money and 3.1 billion yuan of domestic investment to
build 15 tourist resorts.
</P>
<P>
The tourism industry in the province has a total fixed asset of
10.4 billion yuan beside that in the resorts, and has 430,000
tourist-industry employees.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981204.0395 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Building Natural-Gas Power Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a
330-million-yuan natural gas power plant has begun in the largest
north China port city of Tianjin, the first of its kind ever built
locally.
</P>
<P>
With some 50,000 square meters of floor space, the Binhai
Natural Gas Power Plant is near a natural gas processing plant and
will be a major consumer of natural gas from the Bohai Sea.
</P>
<P>
The power plant will install units with a combined capacity of
250,000 kw, and is expected to ease local power supply shortages.
</P>
<P>
The oil fields in western part of the Bohai Sea went into
operation in 1997 and have an annual production capacity of
500,000 tons of oil and up to 400,000 cubic meters of natural
gas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
