<DOCNO> XIE19981204.0396 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Builds Shortcut Railway to Sea Coast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region in southwest China has built a new shortcut railway to the
sea coast which will greatly facilitate trade.
</P>
<P>
The 156-kilometer-long rail line begins at the major crossroad
station of Litang in the north and ends at the port of Qinzhou in
the south. The railway, which took 19 months to build and became
operational on early this week, can accommodate some 15 million
tons of cargo a year.
</P>
<P>
This new line shortens the mountainous western areas' distance
to the sea coast by around 100 kilometers on average and was built
at a cost of 1.03 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
