<HEADLINE> Zen-Ruffinen Confirmed FIFA General Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Former international referee
Michel Zen-Ruffinen of Switzerland was confirmed FIFA general
secretary on Thursday, according to reports from Zurich.
</P>
<P>
Zen-Ruffinen, acting general secretary since April, succeeded
Sepp Blatter, who was elected FIFA president in June.
</P>
<P>
He joined FIFA in 1986, taking charge of refereeing.
</P>
<P>
Zen-Ruffinen, a lawyer, was also in charge of FIFA's legal
affairs before being appointed deputy general secretary in 1995.
