<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chilean Air Force to Maintain Ties with Spanish, UK Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The Chilean Air Force (FACH)
will go ahead with its defense projects with British and Spanish
companies, despite the detention in London of retired General
Augusto Pinochet requested by a Spanish magistrate.
</P>
<P>
FACH Commander-in-Chief General Fernando Rojas Vender said on
Thursday that "it is not opportune yet to take a decision" on the
eventual suspension of the arms order or joint projects with Spain
and the United Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
"We have a great friendship with both countries and as long as
the theme is maintained in the political field we will follow
whatever the government decides on the matter of foreign
relations," said Rojas.
</P>
<P>
He also said that political and commercial matters must be
separated "since it takes much work to construct these friendships
with the armed forces."
</P>
<P>
The FACH is now working with Spain on a satellite project and
considering the acquisition of Casa 295 planes from Spain.
</P>
<P>
It has also selected, together with other three models (two
from the United States and one French), a British-Swedish aircraft
to replace the Chilean fighter aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The model is the Gripen JAS-39, of SAAB.A.B. and British
Aerospace, whose possible acquisition is "temporarily frozen"
because of budgetary reasons, according to FACH sources.
</P>
<P>
"We have to wait for the outcome of the events. We need to be
cautious and follow the line adopted by the government of
President Eduardo Frei about these matters," said Rojas.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet was detained in London 48 days ago at the request of
Spanish Judge Baltasar Garzon, who wants him extradited to face
charges of crimes against humanity committed under his military
government from 1973 to 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981204.0407 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Paging Market Highly Competitive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese paging market is
becoming maliciously competitive with some companies attracting
customers away from other companies by selling at or bellow cost,
according to officials of the Ministry of Information Industry
(MII).
</P>
<P>
China's paging market has boomed since 1994, when the country
opened up the sector to private companies. By September this year,
pager users had been increasing by 10 million a year. Currently,
China has 65 million pager users.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, there are over 2,000 paging companies nationwide,
"one-third of which are too small in size" and there are too many
of them, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
They stressed at a recent national meeting on the paging
industry that it forbids any unfair-competition practices that go
so far as to give away free pagers and charge only service fees.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has already adopted measures that make it
technically more complicated for pager users to change frequencies.
</P>
<P>
MII officials said it encourages mergers among paging
companies, and that this should be the future direction for the
paging industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981204.0408 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brian Kidd Factfile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 3 (Xinhua) -- Following is a factfile of
Brian Kidd, who was appointed manager of English Premier League
club Blackburn Rovers on Thursday:
</P>
<P>
Born: Manchester, May 29, 1949
</P>
<P>
Career:
</P>
<P>
1966 - Joined Manchester United as apprentice professional.
</P>
<P>
1967 - August 12 - Aged 18, made United debut in 3-3 draw with
Tottenham Hotspur in Charity Shield. One week later made league
debut for United in 3-1 away defeat at Everton, a club he later
joined.
</P>
<P>
1968 - May 29 - On his 19th birthday scores Manchester
United's third goal in their 4-1 win over Benfica in the European
Cup Final at Wembley Stadium
</P>
<P>
1974 - After total of 264 matches and 70 goals for United,
joins Arsenal for 110,000 pounds.
</P>
<P>
1976 - July -- Returned to Manchester, signing for City in
110,000 pounds deal.
</P>
<P>
1979 - March -- Left City for Everton where he became one of
the few players to complete a rare trio of playing in a
Manchester derby, a North London derby and a Merseyside derby.
</P>
<P>
1980 - May -- After scoring 12 goals for Everton in 40 league
matches, joined Bolton scoring 14 goals in 43 league appearances
before moving to the United States in 1981.
</P>
<P>
1985 - Began managerial career as player-manager of non-league
Barrow before joining Preston as assistant manager.
</P>
<P>
1985 - December -- Appointed Preston manager
</P>
<P>
1986 - March -- Resigned as Preston manager
</P>
<P>
1989 - Returned to Manchester United as a coach
</P>
<P>
1991 - Appointed assistant manager by Alex Ferguson
</P>
<P>
1998 - December 3 -- Named as Blackburn Rovers manager
</P>
</TEXT>
