<HEADLINE> Work-Linked Training to Be Launched in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 3 (Xinhua) -- The 15 European Union (EU)
countries have agreed to promote European pathways in work-linked
training in a bid to encourage the mobility of people in
vocational training and to link schools and business training
centers throughout the union area.
</P>
<P>
In the framework of the achievement of the union's internal
market and the implementation of a knowledge-based Europe, the EU
said here Thursday, the mobility of people has become an
increasing element of European citizenship as well as an
intercultural and social instrument.
</P>
<P>
However, the activity of the EU cannot be restricted to simply
encourage the mobility of people in training, the EU commission
said. Conditions must also be created in order to provide maximum
efficiency to these training schemes and proper visibility must
also be given to training periods accomplished in member states.
</P>
<P>
Ministers of the 15 EU member states formally approved the
action program Wednesday. The European pathway in work-linked
training also includes apprenticeship, which emphasizes
complementarity of schools and businesses for European people to
learn knowledge and skills, the commission said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
